post_text:
Join us next week in honoring the memory of Denise Zeman by participating in our Spirit of Giving Week and supporting the Shoes That Fit Organization. If able, we would appreciate coin or dollar contributions to support this great cause. https://www.shoesthatfit.org/

Spirit of Giving Week: Zeman’s Kicks for Kids
December 11-December 15
Monday - Gym Shoe Day
Tuesday - College Sports Day
Wednesday - Track/Athletic Pants Day
Thursday - Sports Themed Hat Day
Friday - Festive Friday! Wear your holiday-themed apparel and accessories!

High Five Friday!

Student Leader of the Month; a student who shows exemplary character through his/her compassion, honesty, trustworthiness, responsibility, optimism, and loyalty in creating a positive school environment at Winfield School. Students are recognized with a certificate, and their picture will be displayed on the ‘Leadership Bulletin Board’ located in the Central building.

Congratulations to the following students who were nominated for the month of October: Vanessa, Nina, Winter Grace, Brook, Elena, Tadeo, Maeve, Soraya, Olivia, Alfredo, Dirk, Ella, Declan, Maggie, Antonia, and Joshua.

post_text: The Winfield Board of Education continues to have an unfilled seat that must be filled within the next 45 days. Please consider volunteering for this 2 year term by submitting a letter of interest and resume to Maureen Panzeca at the District Office in the Primary School by May 18, 2017. Interviews will take place on May 25, 2017 at the Regular Board of Education meeting during Closed Session. For more information, contact Maureen Panzeca at mpanzeca@winfield34.org.

post_text:
The Winfield Energy Squad was invited to the Energizing Student Potential Celebration at the Field Museum. All of the schools who received this grant were invited to the event. Winfield was one of a select few who were asked to take the stage and present their project. The students did an outstanding job!

Congratulations to Winfield Central School who has been named the Illinois Junior Rookie of the Year and the National Junior Rookie of the Year for their Youth Awards submission. Student delegates will be attending the National Youth Awards Conference in Washington DC this June to accept the award.
(Not pictured Kelley)
text:
The Winfield Energy Squad was invited to the Energizing Student Potential Celebration at the Field Museum. All of the schools who received this grant were invited to the event. Winfield was one of a select few who were asked to take the stage and present their project. The students did an outstanding job!

Congratulations to Winfield Central School who has been named the Illinois Junior Rookie of the Year and the National Junior Rookie of the Year for their Youth Awards submission. Student delegates will be attending the National Youth Awards Conference in Washington DC this June to accept the award.
(Not pictured Kelley)

Congratulations to Dr. Kell who has been named the 2017 Superintendent of Distinction by her colleagues in the Du Page Region of the Illinois Association of School Administrators (IASA). An awards luncheon was held on April 24th in Springfield, hosted by State Superintendent Dr. Tony Smith.
